<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-26-0382 </DOCNO><TEXT>The various actions of the AFME (French Agency for Energy Conservation)in the french overseas territories (Reunion, Martinique, Guadeloupe,Guyana, New Caledonia, Polynesy, etc...) are reviewed; for each zone,the different projects and realizations are described and analysed (investment,planning and costs) since 1981. The main actions are concerned with domesticwater solar heating, photovoltaic electricity, mini-hydraulics, energyconservation in the residential, industrial, transportation sectors,and bioclimatic households.</TEXT></DOC>